<eesti>1. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 1 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse reguleerimisala </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of application of Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolev seadus s&auml;testab t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna suhtes esitatavad t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse n&otilde;uded, t&ouml;&ouml;andja ja t&ouml;&ouml;taja kohustused tervisele ohutu t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna loomisel, t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse korralduse ettev&otilde;tte ja asutuse ning riigi tasandil, asjaomaste vaidluste lahendamise korra ning vastutuse t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) This Act provides the occupational health and safety requirements for the working environment, the duties of employers and workers in creating a working environment which is safe for health, the organisation of occupational health and safety in enterprises and agencies and at state level, the procedure for resolution of corresponding disputes, and liability for non-compliance with the occupational health and safety requirements. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esolev seadus kehtib k&otilde;igil tegevusaladel, v&auml;lja arvatud juhud, kui t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse n&otilde;uded kaitsev&auml;e, Kaitseliidu, politsei ja piirivalve, samuti p&auml;&auml;steasutuste tegevuse kohta on eriseadustega s&auml;testatud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) This Act applies to all areas of activity, except for cases where the occupational health and safety requirements for the activities of the armed forces, National Defence League, police and border guard, and for the activities of the rescue service agencies are regulated otherwise by specific Acts. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tervishoid ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutus </eesti>
<inglise>Occupational health and safety </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolevas seaduses m&otilde;istetakse t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiuna t&ouml;&ouml;taja tervisekahjustuse v&auml;ltimiseks t&ouml;&ouml;korraldus- ja meditsiiniabin&otilde;ude rakendamist, t&ouml;&ouml; kohandamist t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;imetele ning t&ouml;&ouml;taja f&uuml;&uuml;silise, vaimse ja sotsiaalse heaolu edendamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, occupational health is the application of work-related organisational and medical measures to prevent damage to the health of workers, adaptation of work to the abilities of workers, and promotion of the physical, mental and social well-being of workers. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esolevas seaduses m&otilde;istetakse t&ouml;&ouml;ohutusena t&ouml;&ouml;korraldusabin&otilde;ude ja tehnikavahendite s&uuml;steemi sellise t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna seisundi saavutamiseks, mis v&otilde;imaldab t&ouml;&ouml;tajal teha t&ouml;&ouml;d oma tervist ohtu seadmata. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) For the purposes of this Act, occupational safety is a system of work-related organisational and technical measures to provide a working environment which enables workers to work without endangering their health. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu- ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutusalase v&auml;lja&otilde;ppe ja t&auml;iend&otilde;ppe korra kehtestab sotsiaalminister oma m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The procedure for training and in-service training in occupational health and safety shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>2. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;keskkond </eesti>
<inglise>Working Environment </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;ldn&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>General requirements </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;keskkond on &uuml;mbrus, milles inimene t&ouml;&ouml;tab. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The working environment is the setting in which people work. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnas toimivad tehnilised, f&uuml;&uuml;sikalised, keemilised, bioloogilised, f&uuml;sioloogilised ja ps&uuml;hholoogilised tegurid ei v&otilde;i ohustada t&ouml;&ouml;taja ega muu t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnas viibiva isiku elu ega tervist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Technical, physical, chemical, biological, physiological and psychological factors present in the working environment shall not endanger the life or health of workers or that of other persons in the working environment. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna f&uuml;&uuml;sikaliste, keemiliste ja bioloogiliste ohutegurite parameetrid peavad vastama piirnormidele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The parameters of physical, chemical and biological risk factors present in the working environment shall comply with limits. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna ohutegurite piirnormid ja ohutegurite parameetrite m&otilde;&otilde;tmise korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The limits for risk factors present in the working environment and the procedure for measuring the parameters of risk factors shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui &otilde;nnetuse v&otilde;i haigestumise ohtu ei saa v&auml;ltida ega piirata tehniliste &uuml;hiskaitsevahenditega v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;korralduslike abin&otilde;udega, annab t&ouml;&ouml;andja t&ouml;&ouml;tajale isikukaitsevahendid. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If it is not possible to prevent or reduce the risk of accident or disease by means of collective technical protective equipment or work-related organisational measures, the employer shall provide workers with personal protective equipment. </inglise>
<eesti>Isikukaitsevahendite valiku ja kasutamise korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>The procedure for the selection and use of personal protective equipment shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;koht </eesti>
<inglise>Workplace </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolevas seaduses m&otilde;istetakse t&ouml;&ouml;kohana f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i &auml;ri&uuml;hingu ettev&otilde;tte, riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse asutuse, mittetulundus&uuml;hingu v&otilde;i sihtasutuse (edaspidi ettev&otilde;te) territooriumil v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;ruumis paiknevat t&ouml;&ouml;tamiskohta ja selle &uuml;mbrust v&otilde;i muid t&ouml;&ouml;tamiskohti, kuhu t&ouml;&ouml;tajal on t&ouml;&ouml;tamise ajal juurdep&auml;&auml;s v&otilde;i kus ta t&ouml;&ouml;tab t&ouml;&ouml;andja loal v&otilde;i korraldusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, a workplace is a place of work and its surroundings on the premises of an enterprise of a sole proprietor or company, a state or local government agency, a non-profit association or a foundation (hereinafter enterprise) or any other places of work to which the worker has access in the course of his or her employment or where he or she works with the permission or on the order of the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andja kujundab ja sisustab t&ouml;&ouml;koha nii, et on v&otilde;imalik v&auml;ltida t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetusi ja tervisekahjustusi ning s&auml;ilitada t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime ja heaolu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employer shall design and furnish workplaces such that it is possible to prevent occupational accidents and damage to health, and to maintain the workers' capacity for work and their well-being. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;protsessiga kaasneb ohtliku suitsu, tolmu, gaasi, auru v&otilde;i vedeliku eraldumine koguses, mis v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;taja tervist kahjustada, tuleb v&auml;ltida heitme levikut t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonda, tagada selle eemaldamine tekkekohast ja muutmine kahjutuks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If in the work process dangerous smoke, dust, gases, vapour or liquids are emitted in doses which may be harmful to the health of workers, the emissions shall be prevented from spreading in the working environment and it shall be ensured that the emissions be removed from the source and be rendered harmless. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Terviseriski v&auml;ltimiseks v&otilde;i v&auml;hendamiseks peavad t&ouml;&ouml;kohas olema kaitse-, p&auml;&auml;ste- ja esmaabivahendid, ohum&auml;rgid ning muud ohutusvahendid. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In order to prevent or reduce health risks, workplaces shall be provided with protective, rescue and first aid equipment, safety signs and other safety equipment. </inglise>
<eesti>Esmaabi korralduse ettev&otilde;ttes ja ohum&auml;rguannete kasutamise n&otilde;uded kehtestab sotsiaalminister oma m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The provision of first aid in enterprises and the requirements for the use of safety signs shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Tegevusalade t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse n&otilde;uded kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The occupational health and safety requirements for specific areas of activity shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;vahend </eesti>
<inglise>Work equipment </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Seadme, t&ouml;&ouml;riista, veoki v&otilde;i muu t&ouml;&ouml;vahendi kasutamine etten&auml;htud otstarbel ning nende paigaldamine, reguleerimine, parandamine, hooldamine, teisaldamine ja puhastamine ei tohi ohustada kasutaja ega teiste isikute tervist ega t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonda. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The use for its intended purpose and the installation, modification, repair, maintenance, handling and cleaning of a device, tool, vehicle or any other work equipment shall not be harmful to the health of its operator or that of other persons, or to the working environment. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andja tagab, et t&ouml;&ouml;vahend sobib t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesande t&auml;itmiseks, vastab kasutaja keham&otilde;&otilde;tmetele ning f&uuml;&uuml;silistele ja vaimsetele v&otilde;imetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employer shall ensure that work equipment is suitable for the work to be carried out and to the dimensions of the body and the physical and mental abilities of its operator. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;andja tagab, et t&ouml;&ouml;taja kasutusse antav t&ouml;&ouml;vahend on projekteeritud ja valmistatud nii, et: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An employer shall ensure that the work equipment made available to workers is designed and manufactured such that: </inglise>
<eesti>1) on t&otilde;kestatud p&auml;&auml;s selle ohualale; </eesti>
<inglise>1) access to its danger zone is prevented; </inglise>
<eesti>2) juhtimisseadis vastab ergonoomian&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>2) its control device conforms to the ergonomic requirements; </inglise>
<eesti>3) k&otilde;rge v&otilde;i madala temperatuuriga pinnad on isoleeritud v&otilde;i piirestatud; </eesti>
<inglise>3) surfaces with high or low temperature are isolated or delineated; </inglise>
<eesti>4) see vastab elektri-, tule- ning plahvatusohutusn&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>4) it conforms to the safety requirements for electricity, fire and explosives; </inglise>
<eesti>5) on v&auml;lditud juhuk&auml;ivitus ning et vajaduse korral on v&otilde;imalik t&ouml;&ouml;vahend v&otilde;i selle osa kohe seisata, energiavarustus katkestada ja ohtlik leke t&otilde;kestada; </eesti>
<inglise>5) accidental starting is prevented and, if necessary, it is possible to stop the equipment or a part thereof immediately, to interrupt its power consumption and to prevent dangerous leakage; </inglise>
<eesti>6) m&uuml;ra, vibratsiooni, kiirguse ja muude ohutegurite tase on v&otilde;imalikult madal ega &uuml;leta piirnorme. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the levels of noise, vibrations, radiation and other risk factors are as low as possible and do not exceed the limits. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;vahendi kasutamise t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse n&otilde;uded kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The occupational health and safety requirements for the use of work equipment shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>F&uuml;&uuml;sikalised ohutegurid </eesti>
<inglise>Physical risk factors </inglise>
<eesti>(1) F&uuml;&uuml;sikalised ohutegurid on &otilde;hu liikumise kiirus ning &otilde;hutemperatuur ja -niiskus, m&uuml;ra ja vibratsioon, ioniseeriv ja mitteioniseeriv kiirgus, elektromagnetv&auml;li ning muud t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnas toimivad t&ouml;&ouml;taja tervist kahjustada v&otilde;ivad f&uuml;&uuml;sikalised tegurid. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The physical risk factors are air velocity, air temperature, air humidity, noise, vibrations, ionizing and non-ionizing radiation, electromagnetic fields and other physical risk factors present in the working environment, which may be harmful to the health of workers. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andja peab rakendama abin&otilde;usid, et f&uuml;&uuml;sikalistest ohuteguritest tulenevat terviseriski v&auml;ltida v&otilde;i viia see v&otilde;imalikult madalale tasemele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employer shall implement measures to prevent health risks arising from physical risk factors or reduce them as much as possible. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;andja tagab, et radioaktiivset ainet kasutades v&otilde;i seda ainet sisaldava t&ouml;&ouml;vahendiga t&ouml;&ouml;tades j&auml;rgitaks kiirgusseaduses (RT I 1997, 37/38, 569; 1998, 97, 1520; 1999, 88, 804) s&auml;testatud ohutusn&otilde;udeid ning et aine v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;vahend ei satuks k&otilde;rvalise isiku k&auml;tte. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An employer shall ensure that the safety requirements provided by the Radiation Act (RT I 1997, 37/38, 569; 1998, 97, 1520; 1999, 88, 804) are observed in the use of radioactive substances or while working with equipment containing radioactive substances, and that such substances or equipment shall not be accessible by unauthorised persons. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Keemilised ohutegurid </eesti>
<inglise>Chemical risk factors </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Keemilised ohutegurid on ettev&otilde;ttes k&auml;ideldavad kemikaaliseaduse (RT I 1998, 47, 697; 1999, 45, 512) &sect; 5 l&otilde;ikes 1 m&auml;&auml;ratletud ohtlikud kemikaalid ja neid sisaldavad materjalid. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The chemical risk factors are dangerous chemicals specified in subsection 5 (1) of the Chemicals Act (RT I 1998, 47, 697; 1999, 45, 512) and materials containing such chemicals, which are handled in an enterprise. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ohtlike kemikaalide ja neid sisaldavate materjalide k&auml;itlemist reguleerivad kemikaaliseadus ja k&auml;esolev seadus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The handling of dangerous chemicals and materials containing such chemicals is regulated by the Chemicals Act and this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ohtlike kemikaalide ja neid sisaldavate materjalide kasutamise n&otilde;uded kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The requirements for the use of dangerous chemicals and materials containing such chemicals shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Bioloogilised ohutegurid </eesti>
<inglise>Biological risk factors </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Bioloogilised ohutegurid on bakterid, viirused, seened, rakukultuurid ja inimese endoparasiidid ning muud bioloogiliselt aktiivsed ained, mis v&otilde;ivad p&otilde;hjustada nakkushaigust, allergiat v&otilde;i m&uuml;rgistust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The biological risk factors are bacteria, viruses, fungi, cell cultures, human endoparasites and other biological agents which may cause an infection, allergy or toxicity. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kaitseks t&ouml;&ouml;kohas toimivate bioloogiliste ohutegurite eest peab t&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;tma tarvitusele abin&otilde;ud, arvestades ohuteguri nakatamisv&otilde;imet. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employer shall implement measures to provide protection from biological risk factors present in the working environment based on the infectiousness of the risk factor. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Bioloogilistest ohuteguritest m&otilde;jutatud t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse n&otilde;uded kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The occupational health and safety requirements for the working environment affected by biological risk factors shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>F&uuml;sioloogilised ja ps&uuml;hholoogilised ohutegurid </eesti>
<inglise>Physiological and psychological risk factors </inglise>
<eesti>(1) F&uuml;sioloogilised ohutegurid on f&uuml;&uuml;silise t&ouml;&ouml; raskus, sama t&uuml;&uuml;pi liigutuste kordumine ning &uuml;lev&auml;simust p&otilde;hjustavad sundasendid ja -liigutused t&ouml;&ouml;s ning muud samalaadsed tegurid, mis v&otilde;ivad aja jooksul viia tervisekahjustuseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The physiological risk factors are heavy physical work, repetitive movements of the same type and physical positions and movements in work which cause fatigue, or other similar factors that may gradually cause damage to health. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ps&uuml;hholoogilised ohutegurid on monotoonne v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;imetele mittevastav t&ouml;&ouml;, halb t&ouml;&ouml;korraldus ja pikaajaline t&ouml;&ouml;tamine &uuml;ksinda ning muud samalaadsed tegurid, mis v&otilde;ivad aja jooksul p&otilde;hjustada muutusi t&ouml;&ouml;taja ps&uuml;&uuml;hilises seisundis. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The psychological risk factors are monotonous work or work not suitable to the abilities of a worker, poor work organisation, working alone for an extended period of time, or other similar factors that may gradually cause changes in the mental state of a worker. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;taja f&uuml;&uuml;silise ja vaimse &uuml;lekoormuse v&auml;ltimiseks peab t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohandama t&ouml;&ouml; t&ouml;&ouml;tajale v&otilde;imalikult sobivaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In order to prevent the physical and mental stress of workers, the employer shall adapt the work to suit the workers as much as possible. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;koha kujundamisel ja t&ouml;&ouml; korraldamisel peab arvestama t&ouml;&ouml;taja kehalisi, vaimseid, soolisi ja ealisi ise&auml;rasusi, tema t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime muutumist t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva v&otilde;i vahetuse jooksul ning v&otilde;imalikku pikaajalist &uuml;ksinda t&ouml;&ouml;tamist. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the designing of a workplace and organisation of work, the physical, mental, gender and age characteristics of the worker, changes in his or her capacity for work during a working day or shift, and the possibility of working alone for an extended period of time shall be taken into account. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Raskuste k&auml;sitsi teisaldamise t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse n&otilde;uded kehtestab sotsiaalminister oma m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The occupational health and safety requirements for the manual handling of loads shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Naist&ouml;&ouml;tajad ning alaealised ja puudega t&ouml;&ouml;tajad </eesti>
<inglise>Female workers, minors and disabled workers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Rasedatele, rinnaga toitvatele naistele, alaealistele ja puudega t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele peab t&ouml;&ouml;andja looma sobivad t&ouml;&ouml;- ja olmetingimused. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer shall create suitable working and rest conditions for pregnant women, women who are breastfeeding, minors and disabled workers. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andja j&auml;rgib rasedate, rinnaga toitvate naiste ja alaealiste t&ouml;&ouml;lerakendamisel nende ohutuse tagamiseks &otilde;igusaktidega s&auml;testatud piiranguid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon assigning work to pregnant women, women who are breastfeeding, or minors, employers shall observe the restrictions provided by legislation to ensure their safety. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud t&ouml;&ouml;- ja teenistussuhteid reguleerivates seadustes s&auml;testatud korras andma tema ettev&otilde;ttes t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetuse v&otilde;i kutsehaiguse tagaj&auml;rjel invaliidistunud t&ouml;&ouml;tajale v&otilde;imaluse j&auml;tkata sobival t&ouml;&ouml;l ettev&otilde;ttes. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An employer is required to enable, pursuant to the procedure provided by Acts regulating employment and service relationships, a worker who has become disabled in the employer's enterprise as a result of an occupational accident or occupational disease to continue work suitable for him or her in the enterprise. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Puudega t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml; ja t&ouml;&ouml;tamiskoht tuleb kohandada tema kehaliste ja vaimsete v&otilde;imetega. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The work and workplace of a disabled worker shall be adapted to his or her physical and mental abilities. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Soodustingimused puudega t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;ks kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Preferential conditions for the work of disabled workers shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) T&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse n&otilde;uded rasedate ja rinnaga toitvate naiste t&ouml;&ouml;ks kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The occupational health and safety requirements for the work of pregnant women and women who are breastfeeding shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;olme </eesti>
<inglise>Non-work rooms </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Olmeruumid on riietus-, pesemis-, tualett- ja puhkeruumid, soojakud v&auml;lit&ouml;&ouml;del, einestamisruumid ning muud elukondlikud ruumid. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Non-work rooms are dressing rooms and washrooms, lavatories, rest areas, rooms for warming up in outdoor work, dining areas and other non-work rooms. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;tajate olmeruumid peavad olema ehitatud ja sisustatud, arvestades t&ouml;&ouml;tingimusi ning t&ouml;&ouml;tajate arvu ja soolist koosseisu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Non-work rooms for workers shall be constructed and furnished based on the working conditions and the number and gender of the workers. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;riietust kandvatele t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele on vaja ette n&auml;ha riietusruumid. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Dressing rooms shall be available for workers if they wear special work clothes. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml; laadist olenevalt peab t&ouml;&ouml;tajal olema v&otilde;imalik kasutada pesemisruumi, mis on varustatud valamute ja/v&otilde;i du&scaron;&scaron;idega ning sooja ja k&uuml;lma veega. </eesti>
<inglise>Based on the nature of the work, washrooms equipped with washbasins and/or showers and with hot and cold water shall be available for workers. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml; laadist olenevalt peab t&ouml;&ouml;tajal olema v&otilde;imalik kasutada puhkeruumi, milles peavad olema lauad ja seljatoega istmed. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Based on the nature of the work, workers must be able to use rest areas that shall be equipped with tables and chairs with backs. </inglise>
<eesti>Rasedatel ja rinnaga toitvatel naistel peab olema v&otilde;imalik puhkeruumis sobivates tingimustes lamada. </eesti>
<inglise>Pregnant women and women who are breastfeeding must be able to lie down in rest areas to rest in appropriate conditions. </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja ja t&ouml;&ouml;taja kohustused ja &otilde;igused </eesti>
<inglise>Obligations and Rights of Employers and Workers </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja tagab t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmise igas t&ouml;&ouml;ga seotud olukorras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer shall ensure compliance with the occupational health and safety requirements in every aspect related to the work. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andja ei tohi lubada t&ouml;&ouml;le asuda t&ouml;&ouml;tajal, kellel puuduvad vajalikud erialateadmised ja oskused ning t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu- ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutusalased teadmised. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employer shall not allow workers to work if they lack necessary professional knowledge and skills, and knowledge about occupational health and safety. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;kohal t&ouml;&ouml;tavad samal ajal v&auml;hemalt kahe t&ouml;&ouml;andja t&ouml;&ouml;tajad, s&otilde;lmivad t&ouml;&ouml;andjad kirjaliku kokkuleppe t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu- ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutusalase &uuml;histegevuse ning iga t&ouml;&ouml;andja vastutuse kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If workers of at least two employers work at the workplace at the same time, the employers shall enter into a written agreement on collective occupational health and safety activities and on the liability of each employer. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;histegevust korraldab peat&ouml;&ouml;ettev&otilde;tja. </eesti>
<inglise>Such collective activities shall be arranged by the main contractor. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui kokkulepet ei ole, vastutavad t&ouml;&ouml;andjad kahju tekkimise korral solidaarselt. </eesti>
<inglise>Failing agreement, the employers shall be solidarily liable for damage. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud &uuml;histegevus t&auml;hendab t&ouml;&ouml;andjate tegevuse koosk&otilde;lastamist ohtlike olukordade v&auml;ltimiseks ning &uuml;ksteise ja oma t&ouml;&ouml;tajate v&otilde;i k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 17 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavolinike teavitamist ohtudest ja ohutusabin&otilde;udest. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The collective activities specified in subsection (3) of this section are co-ordinated activities of employers to prevent dangerous situations, and notification of each other and their workers or working environment representatives specified in subsection 17 (1) of this Act of risks and safety measures. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&ouml;&ouml;andja ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajad on kohustatud ohutu t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna nimel tegema koost&ouml;&ouml;d. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Employers and workers are required to co-operate in the creation of a safe working environment. </inglise>
<eesti>Selleks t&ouml;&ouml;andja konsulteerib t&ouml;&ouml;tajate v&otilde;i nende usaldusisiku ja t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavolinikega igas t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnaga seotud k&uuml;simuses, t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna parandamise abin&otilde;ude kavandamisel arvestab nende ettepanekutega ning kaasab nad kavandatu elluviimisele. </eesti>
<inglise>For this purpose, employers shall consult workers or their representatives, and working environment representatives in any issue relating to the working environment, take into account their proposals in planning for measures to improve the working environment and invite them to participate in the implementation of such plans. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) T&ouml;&ouml;andja tagab, et teise ettev&otilde;tte t&ouml;&ouml;andja, kelle t&ouml;&ouml;tajad osalevad tema ettev&otilde;tte t&ouml;&ouml;s, on teadlik ettev&otilde;tte tegevusega seotud ohtudest ja nende v&auml;ltimise abin&otilde;udest ning et need t&ouml;&ouml;tajad on t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu- ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutusalaselt juhendatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) An employer shall ensure that employers of workers from other enterprises engaged in work in the employer's enterprise receive information concerning the risks pertaining to the activities of the enterprise and preventive measures and that such workers have received instructions in occupational health and safety. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustused ja &otilde;igused </eesti>
<inglise>Obligations and rights of employers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer is required to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) viima l&auml;bi s&uuml;stemaatilist t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna sisekontrolli, mille k&auml;igus ta kavandab, korraldab ja j&auml;lgib t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse olukorda ettev&otilde;ttes; </eesti>
<inglise>1) conduct regular internal controls of the working environment to plan, organise and monitor the occupational health and safety situation in the enterprise; </inglise>
<eesti>2) vaatama igal aastal l&auml;bi t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna sisekontrolli korralduse ja anal&uuml;&uuml;sima selle tulemusi ning vajaduse korral kohandama abin&otilde;ud muutunud olukorrale; </eesti>
<inglise>2) review the organisation of internal control of the working environment annually and analyse its results and, if necessary, adjust measures to the changed situation; </inglise>
<eesti>3) viima l&auml;bi t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna riskianal&uuml;&uuml;si, mille k&auml;igus ta selgitab v&auml;lja t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna ohutegurid, m&otilde;&otilde;dab nende parameetrid ning hindab ohutegurite m&otilde;ju t&ouml;&ouml;tajate tervisele; </eesti>
<inglise>3) conduct a risk assessment of the working environment to ascertain the risk factors present in the working environment, measure their parameters and assess the effect of the risk factors on the health of workers; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna riskianal&uuml;&uuml;si alusel koostama kirjaliku tegevuskava, milles n&auml;hakse ette ennetusabin&otilde;ud terviseriski v&auml;ltimiseks v&otilde;i v&auml;hendamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) based on the risk assessment of the working environment, prepare a written action plan designating the measures to prevent or reduce health risks; </inglise>
<eesti>5) viima l&auml;bi uue t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna riskianal&uuml;&uuml;si, kui t&ouml;&ouml;tingimused on muutunud ja t&ouml;&ouml;vahendeid v&otilde;i tehnoloogiat on uuendatud; </eesti>
<inglise>5) conduct a new risk assessment of the working environment if the working conditions have changed and the work equipment or technology has been upgraded; </inglise>
<eesti>6) teavitama t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavolinike, t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogu liikmete ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate usaldusisikute kaudu ohuteguritest, t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna riskianal&uuml;&uuml;si tulemustest ning tervisekahjustuste v&auml;ltimiseks rakendatavatest abin&otilde;udest; </eesti>
<inglise>6) notify the workers of the risk factors, the results of risk assessments of the working environment and of the measures to be implemented in order to prevent damage to health, through working environment representatives, members of the working environment council and workers' representatives; </inglise>
<eesti>6 (1)) rakendama t&ouml;&ouml;taja tervisekahjustuse v&auml;ltimiseks ja k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 6-9 loetletud t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna ohutegurite m&otilde;ju neutraliseerimiseks t&ouml;&ouml;- ja kollektiivlepingutes s&auml;testatud abin&otilde;usid; </eesti>
<inglise>6 (1)) apply measures provided for in employment contracts and collective agreements to prevent damage to the health of workers and neutralise the effect of the risk factors specified in &sect;&sect; 6 - 9 of this Act </inglise>
<eesti>(14.06.2000 j&otilde;ust.21.07.2000 - RT I 2000, 55, 362) </eesti>
<inglise>(14.06.2000 entered into force 21.07.2000 - RT I 2000, 55, 362) </inglise>
<eesti>7) korraldama t&ouml;&ouml;tajate tervise kontrollimise ja muude t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiuteenuste osutamise kas ettev&otilde;tte t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiuteenistuse kaudu v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiuteenistuse v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiuarstiga s&otilde;lmitud lepingu alusel ning kandma sellega seotud kulud; </eesti>
<inglise>7) arrange for the health surveillance of workers and provision of other occupational health services either through the occupational health service of the enterprise or based on a contract entered into with an occupational health service or occupational health doctor, and to cover the expenses relating thereto; </inglise>
<eesti>7 (1)) korraldama &ouml;&ouml;ajal t&ouml;&ouml;tavatele isikutele tervisekontrolli enne t&ouml;&ouml;leasumist ning regulaarsete vaheaegade j&auml;rel t&ouml;&ouml;tamise ajal; </eesti>
<inglise>7 (1)) organise medical examinations for employees who work during night time before they start work and with regular intervals during work; </inglise>
<eesti>(24.01.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 17, 78) </eesti>
<inglise>(24.01.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 17, 78) </inglise>
<eesti>8) m&auml;&auml;rama ettev&otilde;ttes esmaabi andmiseks t&ouml;&ouml;tajad ja korraldama neile t&ouml;&ouml;andja kulul v&auml;lja&otilde;ppe. </eesti>
<inglise>8) designate workers in the enterprise for the provision of first aid and arrange training for them at the employer's expense. </inglise>
<eesti>Mitme all&uuml;ksuse v&otilde;i vahetustega t&ouml;&ouml; korral peab igas all&uuml;ksuses v&otilde;i vahetuses olema kohal v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks esmaabi anda oskav t&ouml;&ouml;taja; </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of work involving several structural units or shift work, at least one worker who is able to provide first aid must be present in each structural unit or on each shift; </inglise>
<eesti>9) tagama k&otilde;igile t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele esmaabivahendite k&auml;ttesaadavuse. </eesti>
<inglise>9) ensure access by all workers to first aid equipment. </inglise>
<eesti>Esmaabivahendeid tuleb hoida n&otilde;uetekohaselt m&auml;rgistatud ja kergesti juurdep&auml;&auml;setavas kohas; </eesti>
<inglise>First aid equipment shall be kept in an easily accessible place that is marked in a required manner; </inglise>
<eesti>10) viima t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;- ja teenistussuhteid reguleerivates seadustes s&auml;testatud korras tema n&otilde;udmisel ja arsti otsuse alusel ajutiselt v&otilde;i alaliselt teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;i kergendama ajutiselt tema t&ouml;&ouml;tingimusi; </eesti>
<inglise>10) at the request of a worker and on the decision of a doctor, transfer the worker to another position temporarily or permanently or ease his or her working conditions temporarily, pursuant to the procedure provided by Acts regulating employment and service relationships; </inglise>
<eesti>11) oma kulul andma t&ouml;&ouml;tajale isikukaitsevahendid, t&ouml;&ouml;riietuse ning puhastus- ja pesemisvahendid, kui t&ouml;&ouml; laad seda n&otilde;uab, ning korraldama t&ouml;&ouml;tajale isikukaitsevahendi kasutamise v&auml;lja&otilde;ppe; </eesti>
<inglise>11) provide, at the employer's expense, workers with personal protective equipment, special work clothes, and cleaning and washing facilities if the nature of the work so requires, and arrange training for workers in the use of personal protective equipment; </inglise>
<eesti>12) tutvustama t&ouml;&ouml;tajale t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse n&otilde;udeid ning kontrollima nende t&auml;itmist; </eesti>
<inglise>12) familiarise workers with the occupational health and safety requirements, and monitor compliance therewith; </inglise>
<eesti>13) korraldama t&ouml;&ouml;tajale enne t&ouml;&ouml;leasumist v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml; vahetamist t&ouml;&ouml;kohale ja ametile vastava t&ouml;&ouml;ohutus- ja t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiualase juhendamise ja v&auml;lja&otilde;ppe. </eesti>
<inglise>13) before a worker commences work or changes job, arrange for the worker to receive occupational health and safety instructions and training corresponding to the worker's position and occupation. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhendamist v&otilde;i v&auml;lja&otilde;pet tuleb korrata, kui t&ouml;&ouml;vahendeid v&otilde;i tehnoloogiat vahetatakse v&otilde;i uuendatakse; </eesti>
<inglise>Instruction or training shall be repeated if the work equipment or technology is changed or upgraded; </inglise>
<eesti>14) koostama ja kinnitama ohutusjuhendi tehtava t&ouml;&ouml; ja kasutatava t&ouml;&ouml;vahendi kohta ning andma t&ouml;&ouml;tajale juhised keskkonna saastamisest hoidumiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>14) prepare and approve safety instructions for the work to be carried out and for the work equipment used, and give instructions to workers to prevent contamination of the environment; </inglise>
<eesti>15) k&otilde;rvaldama t&ouml;&ouml;lt alkoholi-, narkootilises v&otilde;i toksilises joobes v&otilde;i ps&uuml;hhotroopse aine olulise m&otilde;ju all oleva t&ouml;&ouml;taja; </eesti>
<inglise>15) suspend a worker from work if he or she is under the influence of alcohol, narcotics or toxic substances or under the significant influence of psychotropic substances; </inglise>
<eesti>16) taotlema enne kohaliku omavalitsuse poolt uuele v&otilde;i rekonstrueeritud ehitisele kasutusloa andmist asukohaj&auml;rgselt t&ouml;&ouml;inspektorilt n&otilde;usoleku selle ehitise kasutuselev&otilde;tmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>16) before the local government grants an authorisation to use a new or reconstructed building, apply for the authorisation of the labour inspector of the location of the enterprise to commence use of the building; </inglise>
<eesti>17) teavitama kirjalikult T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohalikku asutust oma tegevusala muutmisest; </eesti>
<inglise>17) notify the regional office of the Labour Inspectorate in writing of a change in the employer's area of activity; </inglise>
<eesti>18) tegema t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori ettekirjutused teatavaks t&ouml;&ouml;tajale, t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavolinikule, t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogu liikmetele, t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnaspetsialistile ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate usaldusisikule; </eesti>
<inglise>18) communicate precepts of labour inspectors to the workers, working environment representatives, members of the working environment council, working environment specialists and workers' representatives; </inglise>
<eesti>19) t&auml;itma t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori ettekirjutusi t&auml;htaegselt ja teavitama t&ouml;&ouml;inspektorit kirjalikult nende t&auml;itmisest. </eesti>
<inglise>19) comply with precepts of labour inspectors in a timely manner and report to the labour inspectors on compliance therewith in writing. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employer has the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) m&auml;&auml;rata t&ouml;&ouml;tajale t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoidu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutust k&auml;sitleva &otilde;igusakti n&otilde;ude rikkumise eest distsiplinaarkaristus t&ouml;&ouml;tajate distsiplinaarvastutuse seaduses (RT I 1993, 26, 441; 1995, 16, 228; 1998, 64/65, 1009) etten&auml;htud korras; </eesti>
<inglise>1) impose a disciplinary penalty on a worker pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the Employees Disciplinary Penalties Act (RT I 1993, 26, 441; 1995, 16, 228; 1998, 64/65, 1009) for a violation of requirements of legislation regulating occupational health and safety; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kehtestada ettev&otilde;ttes &otilde;igusaktides etten&auml;htust rangemaid t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse n&otilde;udeid. </eesti>
<inglise>2) establish more stringent occupational health and safety requirements in the enterprise than those prescribed by legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja kohustused ja &otilde;igused </eesti>
<inglise>Obligations and rights of workers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;taja on kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A worker is required to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) osalema ohutu t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna loomisel, j&auml;rgides t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse n&otilde;udeid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) contribute to the creation of a safe working environment, observing the occupational health and safety requirements; </inglise>
<eesti>2) j&auml;rgima t&ouml;&ouml;andja kehtestatud t&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaja korraldust; </eesti>
<inglise>2) observe the working and rest time regime established by the employer; </inglise>
<eesti>3) l&auml;bima tervisekontrolli vastavalt kehtestatud korrale; </eesti>
<inglise>3) undergo health surveillance pursuant to the established procedure; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kasutama etten&auml;htud isikukaitsevahendeid ning hoidma neid t&ouml;&ouml;korras; </eesti>
<inglise>4) use prescribed personal protective equipment and keep it in working order; </inglise>
<eesti>5) tagama vastavalt v&auml;lja&otilde;ppele ja t&ouml;&ouml;andja antud juhistele, et tema t&ouml;&ouml; ei ohustaks tema enda ega teiste elu ja tervist ega saastaks keskkonda; </eesti>
<inglise>5) ensure in accordance with his or her training and the employer's instructions that his or her work is not harmful to his or her own life or health or that of other persons, and does not contaminate the environment; </inglise>
<eesti>6) kohe teatama t&ouml;&ouml;andjale v&otilde;i tema esindajale ja t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavolinikule ohtlikust olukorrast, t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetusest, samuti tema enda terviseh&auml;irest; </eesti>
<inglise>6) promptly notify the employer or the employer's representative and the working environment representative of a dangerous situation, occupational accident and his or her health disorders; </inglise>
<eesti>7) t&auml;itma t&ouml;&ouml;andja, t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnaspetsialisti, t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiuarsti, t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori ja t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavoliniku t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu- ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutusalase korralduse. </eesti>
<inglise>7) comply with the occupational health and safety orders of the employer, working environment specialist, occupational health doctor, labour inspector or working environment representative. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;tajal on keelatud t&ouml;&ouml;tada alkoholi-, narkootilises v&otilde;i toksilises joobes v&otilde;i ps&uuml;hhotroopse aine olulise m&otilde;ju all. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) It is prohibited for workers to work while under the influence of alcohol, narcotics or toxic substances or under the significant influence of psychotropic substances. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 esitatud n&otilde;uete rikkumise korral kannab t&ouml;&ouml;taja vastutust t&ouml;&ouml;tajate distsiplinaarvastutuse seaduse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A worker shall bear liability for a violation of the requirements specified in subsections (1) and (2) of this section pursuant to the Employees Disciplinary Penalties Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu- ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutusalased kohustused ei vabasta t&ouml;&ouml;andjat asjaomasest vastutusest. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The occupational health and safety obligations of workers shall not discharge the employer from liability in this field. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&ouml;&ouml;tajal on &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A worker has the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) n&otilde;uda t&ouml;&ouml;andjalt t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse n&otilde;uetele vastavaid t&ouml;&ouml;tingimusi ning &uuml;his- ja isikukaitsevahendeid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) demand that the employer provide working conditions and collective and personal protective equipment conforming to the occupational health and safety requirements; </inglise>
<eesti>2) saada teavet t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna ohuteguritest, t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna riskianal&uuml;&uuml;si tulemustest, tervisekahjustuste v&auml;ltimiseks rakendatavatest abin&otilde;udest, tervisekontrolli tulemustest ja t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori ettekirjutusest t&ouml;&ouml;andjale; </eesti>
<inglise>2) receive information on risk factors present in the working environment, the results of risk assessments of the working environment, the measures implemented to prevent damage to health, the results of health surveillance, and precepts of the labour inspector addressed to the employer; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&otilde;sise, &auml;hvardava v&otilde;i v&auml;ltimatu &otilde;nnetusohu korral peatada t&ouml;&ouml; ning lahkuda oma t&ouml;&ouml;kohalt v&otilde;i ohtlikult alalt; </eesti>
<inglise>3) in the event of a serious, imminent or unavoidable risk of accident, stop work and leave his or her workplace or the dangerous area; </inglise>
<eesti>4) keelduda t&ouml;&ouml;st v&otilde;i peatada t&ouml;&ouml;, mille t&auml;itmine seab ohtu tema v&otilde;i teiste isikute tervise v&otilde;i ei v&otilde;imalda t&auml;ita keskkonnaohutuse n&otilde;udeid, teatades sellest viivitamata t&ouml;&ouml;andjale v&otilde;i tema esindajale ja t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavolinikule; </eesti>
<inglise>4) refuse to carry out work or to stop work if it is dangerous to his or her health or that of other persons or does not allow to comply with environmental safety requirements, and promptly notify the employer or the employer's representative and working environment representative thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>5) n&otilde;uda t&ouml;&ouml;andjalt arsti otsuse alusel enda &uuml;leviimist ajutiselt v&otilde;i alaliselt teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;i oma t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste ajutist kergendamist; </eesti>
<inglise>5) on the decision of a doctor, demand that the employer transfer him or her to another position temporarily or permanently or that the employer ease his or her working conditions temporarily; </inglise>
<eesti>5 (1)) n&otilde;uda enda &uuml;leviimist sobivale p&auml;evasele t&ouml;&ouml;le, kui &ouml;&ouml;ajal t&ouml;&ouml;tamine on isikule arsti otsuse alusel tervise t&otilde;ttu vastun&auml;idustatud ning t&ouml;&ouml;andjal on v&otilde;imalik t&ouml;&ouml;tajat vastavale t&ouml;&ouml;le &uuml;le viia; </eesti>
<inglise>5 (1)) to request his or her transfer to suitable day-time work if, by decision of a doctor, the employee's working during night time is inadvisable for reasons of health and the employer has the possibility to transfer the employee to such position; </inglise>
<eesti>(24.01.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 17, 78) </eesti>
<inglise>(24.01.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 17, 78) </inglise>
<eesti>6) saada t&ouml;&ouml;st p&otilde;hjustatud tervisekahjustuse eest h&uuml;vitist vastavalt Vabariigi Valitsuse kehtestatud korrale; </eesti>
<inglise>6) receive compensation for damage caused to his or her health by the work, pursuant to the procedure established by the Government of the Republic; </inglise>
<eesti>7) p&ouml;&ouml;rduda t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavoliniku, t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogu liikmete, t&ouml;&ouml;tajate usaldusisiku ja asukohaj&auml;rgse t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori poole, kui tema arvates t&ouml;&ouml;andja poolt rakendatavad abin&otilde;ud ja antud vahendid ei taga t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna ohutust. </eesti>
<inglise>7) contact working environment representatives, members of the working environment council, workers' representatives and the labour inspector of the location of the enterprise if, in his or her opinion, the measures implemented and the equipment provided by the employer do not ensure the safety of the working environment. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;nnetusoht </eesti>
<inglise>Risk of accident </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolevas seaduses m&otilde;istetakse &otilde;nnetusjuhtumina ettev&otilde;ttes toimuvat raske tagaj&auml;rjega &otilde;nnetust, mis v&otilde;ib ohustada t&ouml;&ouml;tajate ja teiste isikute elu ja tervist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, an accident is a serious accident which occurs in an enterprise and may endanger the life or health of workers or that of other persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) V&otilde;imaliku &otilde;nnetusjuhtumi puhuks on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) To prepare for a possible accident, an employer is required to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) korraldama side&uuml;hendused ettev&otilde;ttev&auml;liste p&auml;&auml;ste- ja h&auml;daabiteenistustega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) arrange contacts with the rescue and emergency services outside the enterprise; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ettev&otilde;tte suurusest ja tegevuse laadist olenevalt m&auml;&auml;rama kindlaks tegevuskava ohualast inimeste v&auml;ljaviimiseks, tulekustutus- ja p&auml;&auml;stet&ouml;&ouml;de tegemiseks ning esmaabi andmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) based on the size and the nature of the activities of the enterprise, prepare an action plan for the evacuation of people from danger areas, fire extinction, performance of rescue work and provision of first aid; </inglise>
<eesti>3) m&auml;&auml;rama ohualast inimeste v&auml;ljaviimise, tulekustutus- ja p&auml;&auml;stet&ouml;&ouml;de tegemise ja esmaabi andmise eest vastutavad t&ouml;&ouml;tajad ning teavitama nendest ettev&otilde;tte t&ouml;&ouml;tajaskonda. </eesti>
<inglise>3) designate workers responsible for the evacuation of people from danger areas, fire extinction, performance of rescue work and provision of first aid and notify the staff of the enterprise of such workers. </inglise>
<eesti>Nende t&ouml;&ouml;tajate arv, v&auml;lja&otilde;pe ja nende k&auml;sutuses olev varustus peavad vastama ettev&otilde;tte suurusele ja ohu erip&auml;rale; </eesti>
<inglise>The number and training of and equipment at the disposal of the designated workers shall be adapted to the size of the enterprise and the nature of the risk; </inglise>
<eesti>4) m&auml;&auml;rama kindlaks seadmete seiskamise ja v&auml;ljal&uuml;litamise korra; </eesti>
<inglise>4) determine the procedure for stopping and switching off equipment; </inglise>
<eesti>5) andma t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele juhised t&ouml;&ouml; peatamiseks ja/v&otilde;i ohualalt lahkumiseks t&otilde;sise ja v&auml;ltimatu &otilde;nnetusohu tekkimisel. </eesti>
<inglise>5) give instructions to workers to stop work and/or leave the danger area in the event of a serious or unavoidable risk of accident. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud &otilde;nnetusohu tekkimise korral teatama ohust ja rakendatavatest abin&otilde;udest v&otilde;imalikult kiiresti k&otilde;igile t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele, kes on v&otilde;i v&otilde;ivad sattuda t&otilde;sisesse ohtu. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In the event of a risk of accident, an employer is required to inform as soon as possible all workers who are or may be exposed to serious danger of the risk involved and of the steps to be taken. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;tajad peavad t&otilde;sise ja &auml;hvardava &otilde;nnetusohu korral v&otilde;tma tarvitusele abin&otilde;ud vastavalt oma teadmistele ja k&auml;ttesaadavatele tehnilistele vahenditele v&otilde;imalike tagaj&auml;rgede v&auml;ltimiseks ka sellisel juhul, kui vahetu &uuml;lemusega ei ole v&otilde;imalik kohe &uuml;hendust saada. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In the event of a serious and imminent risk of accident, workers shall take steps in the light of their knowledge and the technical means at their disposal to avoid the possible consequences even if their immediate superior cannot be contacted at once. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&otilde;sise ja v&auml;ltimatu ohu korral peavad t&ouml;&ouml;tajad t&ouml;&ouml;kohalt lahkuma kiirelt ja ohutult. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) In the event of a serious and unavoidable danger, workers shall leave their workplaces quickly and safely. </inglise>
<eesti>Selleks peavad evakuatsioonip&auml;&auml;sud ja -teed olema takistuseta ning varustatud piisava turvavalgustusega. </eesti>
<inglise>For this purpose, emergency exits and routes must remain clear and be equipped with sufficient emergency lighting. </inglise>
<eesti>T&otilde;sise ja v&auml;ltimatu ohu korral oma t&ouml;&ouml;kohalt v&otilde;i ohtlikult alalt omavoliliselt lahkunud t&ouml;&ouml;tajat ei tohi selle eest karistada ega asetada ebasoodsasse olukorda. </eesti>
<inglise>Workers who, in the event of a serious and unavoidable danger, leave their workplaces or a danger area without permission shall not be punished or placed at any disadvantage. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) T&ouml;&ouml;andja ei tohi kutsuda t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid t&ouml;&ouml;d j&auml;tkama enne, kui oht on k&otilde;rvaldatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) An employer shall not ask workers to resume work until the danger is eliminated. </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse korraldus </eesti>
<inglise>Organisation of Occupational Health and Safety </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnaspetsialist </eesti>
<inglise>Working environment specialist </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnaspetsialist on t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna alal p&auml;dev insener v&otilde;i muu t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna&otilde;petust saanud spetsialist ettev&otilde;ttes, keda t&ouml;&ouml;andja on volitanud t&auml;itma t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu- ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutusalaseid &uuml;lesandeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A working environment specialist is an engineer competent in the sphere of working environment or any other specialist in an enterprise who has received training concerning the working environment and whom the employer has authorised to perform occupational health and safety duties. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andja peab t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnaspetsialisti m&auml;&auml;rama oma t&ouml;&ouml;tajate hulgast v&otilde;i p&auml;deva isiku puudumisel v&otilde;tma t&ouml;&ouml;le v&auml;ljastpoolt ettev&otilde;tet. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employer shall appoint a working environment specialist from among the employer's workers or, in the absence of a competent person, hire a working environment specialist from outside the enterprise. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnaspetsialisti ametisse m&auml;&auml;ramine v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;tmine ei vabasta t&ouml;&ouml;andjat vastutusest t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse valdkonnas. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The appointment to office or hiring of a working environment specialist shall not discharge the employer from liability in the field of occupational health and safety. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnaspetsialist peab tundma t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoidu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutust reguleerivaid &otilde;igusakte ja ettev&otilde;tte t&ouml;&ouml;tingimusi, neid j&auml;lgima ja kontrollima ning v&otilde;tma tarvitusele abin&otilde;ud t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna ohutegurite m&otilde;ju v&auml;hendamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A working environment specialist shall be familiar with the legislation regulating occupational health and safety and with the working conditions in the enterprise, monitor and inspect them and take measures to reduce the effect of risk factors present in the working environment. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnaspetsialist on kohustatud peatama ajutiselt t&ouml;&ouml; ohtlikus t&ouml;&ouml;l&otilde;igus v&otilde;i keelama ohtliku t&ouml;&ouml;vahendi kasutamise, kui on tekkinud otsene oht t&ouml;&ouml;taja elule v&otilde;i tervisele ja kui ohtu ei ole v&otilde;imalik muul viisil k&otilde;rvaldada. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A working environment specialist is required to temporarily stop work in a dangerous stage of work or prohibit the use of dangerous work equipment if there is a direct risk of harm to the life or health of a worker or if it is not possible to eliminate the risk in any other manner. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Ohutu t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna loomiseks ning t&ouml;&ouml;tajate t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime s&auml;ilitamiseks teeb t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnaspetsialist koost&ouml;&ouml;d t&ouml;&ouml;tajatega ning t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavoliniku, t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogu, t&ouml;&ouml;tajate usaldusisiku ja t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiuarstiga. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) In order to create a safe working environment and maintain workers' capacity for work, a working environment specialist shall co-operate with workers and working environment representatives, the working environment council, workers' representatives and occupational health doctors. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) T&ouml;&ouml;andja varustab t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnaspetsialisti t&ouml;&ouml;ks vajalike vahenditega. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) An employer shall provide a working environment specialist with equipment necessary for his or her work. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) T&ouml;&ouml;andja teavitab t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnaspetsialisti t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna ohuteguritest, nende v&auml;ltimiseks rakendatavatest ja k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 15 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud abin&otilde;udest. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) An employer shall notify a working environment specialist of the risk factors present in the working environment, preventive measures and of the measures specified in subsection 15 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) T&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;ib ise t&auml;ita t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnaspetsialisti kohustusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) An employer may perform the duties of a working environment specialist himself or herself. </inglise>
<eesti>(10) T&ouml;&ouml;andja teavitab m&auml;&auml;ratud t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnaspetsialistist T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohalikku asutust kirjalikult k&uuml;mne p&auml;eva jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(10) An employer shall notify the regional office of the Labour Inspectorate of the appointment of a working environment specialist in writing within ten days. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavolinik </eesti>
<inglise>Working environment representative </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavolinik on t&ouml;&ouml;tajate valitud esindaja t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse k&uuml;simustes ning tema volitused kehtivad kaks aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A working environment representative is a representative elected by workers in occupational health and safety issues, whose term of authority is two years. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kuni k&uuml;mne t&ouml;&ouml;tajaga ettev&otilde;ttes valivad t&ouml;&ouml;tajad enda hulgast &uuml;he t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavoliniku. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In an enterprise with up to ten workers, the workers shall elect one working environment representative from among themselves. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ettev&otilde;ttes, mis koosneb mitmest all&uuml;ksusest v&otilde;i kus vahetuses t&ouml;&ouml;tab korraga &uuml;le k&uuml;mne t&ouml;&ouml;taja, valivad t&ouml;&ouml;tajad igasse all&uuml;ksusse v&otilde;i vahetusse &uuml;he t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavoliniku. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In an enterprise which comprises several structural units or in which more than ten workers work on a shift at the same time, the workers shall elect one working environment representative for every structural unit or shift. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;andja korraldab t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavolinike valimisteks t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &uuml;ldkoosoleku, milles k&otilde;igil t&ouml;&ouml;tajatel on v&otilde;imalik osaleda kas otse v&otilde;i lihtkirjalikult volitatud isiku kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) To elect working environment representatives, an employer shall call a general meeting of workers, in which all workers may participate either directly or through a person authorised by an unattested authorisation. </inglise>
<eesti>Valimised loetakse toimunuks, kui neis on osalenud v&auml;hemalt 50 protsenti k&otilde;igist t&ouml;&ouml;tajatest. </eesti>
<inglise>An election is deemed to have been held if at least 50 per cent of all workers participated therein. </inglise>
<eesti>Valimiste kord s&auml;testatakse kollektiivlepingus v&otilde;i muus t&ouml;&ouml;andja ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate vahelises kirjalikus lepingus. </eesti>
<inglise>The election procedure is provided by a collective agreement or any other written contract between the employer and workers. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja teeb valitud t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavolinike nimed ja ametid T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohalikule asutusele teatavaks valimistest arvates k&uuml;mne p&auml;eva jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>The employer shall notify the regional office of the Labour Inspectorate of the names and positions of the elected working environment representatives within ten days after the election. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavoliniku kohustused on: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The obligations of a working environment representative are to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) j&auml;lgida, et t&ouml;&ouml;kohas oleksid rakendatud t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse abin&otilde;ud ning et t&ouml;&ouml;tajad oleksid varustatud t&ouml;&ouml;korras isikukaitsevahenditega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) monitor that occupational health and safety measures are implemented at the workplaces and that the workers are provided with personal protective equipment which is in working order; </inglise>
<eesti>2) osaleda oma t&ouml;&ouml;l&otilde;igus toimunud t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetuse ja kutsehaigestumise uurimisel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) participate in the investigation of an occupational accident or disease in his or her area of work; </inglise>
<eesti>3) teatada ohuolukorrast v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnas avastatud puudusest viivitamata t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele ja t&ouml;&ouml;andjale v&otilde;i tema esindajale ning n&otilde;uda t&ouml;&ouml;andjalt puuduse k&otilde;rvaldamist v&otilde;imalikult l&uuml;hikese aja jooksul; </eesti>
<inglise>3) notify the workers and the employer or the employer's representative promptly of a dangerous situation or deficiencies discovered in the working environment, and demand that the employer eliminate the deficiencies as soon as possible; </inglise>
<eesti>4) tunda t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele kohustuslikke juhendeid ja &otilde;igusakte; </eesti>
<inglise>4) be familiar with the instructions and legislation mandatory for workers; </inglise>
<eesti>5) j&auml;lgida, et t&ouml;&ouml;tajad saaksid t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse valdkonnas vajalikud teadmised, juhendamise ja v&auml;lja&otilde;ppe. </eesti>
<inglise>5) monitor that the workers receive necessary knowledge, instructions and training in the field of occupational health and safety. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavolinikul on &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A working environment representative has the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) n&otilde;uda t&ouml;&ouml;andjalt etten&auml;htud t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse abin&otilde;ude rakendamist, t&ouml;&ouml;tajate varustamist t&ouml;&ouml;korras isikukaitsevahenditega ning teha ettepanekuid ohuallika k&otilde;rvaldamiseks ja t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna parandamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) demand that the employer implement prescribed occupational health and safety measures and provide the workers with personal protective equipment which is in working order, and to make proposals to remove the sources of danger and improve the working environment; </inglise>
<eesti>2) p&auml;&auml;seda ettev&otilde;ttes k&otilde;igisse t&ouml;&ouml;kohtadesse, saada t&ouml;&ouml;andjalt oma kohustuste t&auml;itmiseks vajalikku teavet ning teavet t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori ettekirjutusest t&ouml;&ouml;andjale; </eesti>
<inglise>2) access all workplaces in the enterprise and receive information from the employer which is necessary for the performance of his or her duties and information concerning precepts addressed by the labour inspector to the employer; </inglise>
<eesti>3) p&ouml;&ouml;rduda asukohaj&auml;rgse t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori poole; </eesti>
<inglise>3) contact the labour inspector of the location of the enterprise; </inglise>
<eesti>4) peatada ajutiselt t&ouml;&ouml; ohtlikus t&ouml;&ouml;l&otilde;igus v&otilde;i keelata ohtliku t&ouml;&ouml;vahendi kasutamine, kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja elu v&otilde;i tervis on otseselt ohus ja kui ohtu ei ole v&otilde;imalik muul viisil k&otilde;rvaldada. </eesti>
<inglise>4) temporarily stop work in a dangerous stage of work or prohibit the use of dangerous work equipment if there is a direct risk of harm to the life or health of workers or if it is not possible to eliminate the risk in any other manner. </inglise>
<eesti>Ohust tuleb viivitamata teatada t&ouml;&ouml;andjale v&otilde;i tema esindajale. </eesti>
<inglise>He or she shall promptly notify the employer or the employer's representative of the risk. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;d ei tohi j&auml;tkata enne, kui oht on k&otilde;rvaldatud. </eesti>
<inglise>Work shall not be resumed until the risk is eliminated. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavolinik ei tohi oma &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmise t&otilde;ttu sattuda ebasoodsasse olukorda, kui ilmneb tema ja t&ouml;&ouml;andja huvide konflikt. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) A working environment representative shall not be placed at any disadvantage due to performance of his or her duties if there is a conflict of interests between him or her and the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) T&ouml;&ouml;andja korraldab oma kulul t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavolinikule tema kohustuste t&auml;itmiseks vajaliku v&auml;lja- v&otilde;i t&auml;iend&otilde;ppe ning v&otilde;imaldab tal oma kohustusi t&auml;ita p&otilde;hit&ouml;&ouml; ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) An employer shall provide, at the employer's expense, training or in-service training for a working environment representative that is necessary for the performance of his or her obligations and shall allow the representative to perform his or her obligations during the working time of the representative's principal job. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavolinikule s&auml;ilitatakse selleks ajaks keskmine t&ouml;&ouml;tasu ja tal on Eesti Vabariigi t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse &sect;-s 94 ning kollektiiv- ja t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus etten&auml;htud tagatised. </eesti>
<inglise>During this period, the working environment representative continues to receive his or her average wages and has the guarantees prescribed in &sect; 94 of the Republic of Estonia Employment Contracts Act, a collective agreement or the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavoliniku &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmise aeg n&auml;hakse ette kollektiivlepingus v&otilde;i muus t&ouml;&ouml;andja ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate kirjalikus lepingus. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) The period for performance of the duties of a working environment representative shall be prescribed in a collective agreement or any other written contract between the employer and workers. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmise aeg s&otilde;ltub ettev&otilde;tte suurusest ja t&ouml;&ouml;tingimustest ning muudest asjaoludest, kuid ta ei tohi olla l&uuml;hem kui kaks tundi n&auml;dalas. </eesti>
<inglise>The period for performance of such duties depends on the size and working conditions of the enterprise and other circumstances but shall not be less than two hours per week. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogu </eesti>
<inglise>Working environment council </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogu on t&ouml;&ouml;andja ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindajate koost&ouml;&ouml;kogu, kus lahendatakse ettev&otilde;tte t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutusega seotud k&uuml;simusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A working environment council is a body for co-operation between an employer and the workers' representatives which resolves occupational health and safety issues in the enterprise. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) V&auml;hemalt 50 t&ouml;&ouml;tajaga ettev&otilde;ttes moodustatakse t&ouml;&ouml;andja algatusel t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogu, kus on v&otilde;rdselt t&ouml;&ouml;andja m&auml;&auml;ratud esindajaid ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate valitud esindajaid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In an enterprise with at least fifty workers, a working environment council shall be set up at the initiative of the employer and shall comprise an equal number of representatives designated by the employer and representatives elected by the workers. </inglise>
<eesti>N&otilde;ukogu liikmeid on v&auml;hemalt neli ja nende volitused kehtivad kaks aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>The council shall comprise at least four members and the term of their authority shall be two years. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindajad valitakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 17 l&otilde;ikes 4 kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Workers' representatives shall be elected pursuant to the procedure established in subsection 17 (4) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) S&otilde;ltuvalt ettev&otilde;tte ohuteguritest ning ettev&otilde;ttes asetleidnud t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetuste ja kutsehaigusjuhtude arvust on T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsioonil &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogu moodustamist ka alla 50 t&ouml;&ouml;tajaga ettev&otilde;ttes. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Labour Inspectorate has the right to demand that a working environment council be set up in an enterprise with less than fifty workers depending on the risk factors present and the number of occupational accidents and cases of occupational disease in the enterprise. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogu valib oma liikmete hulgast esimehe ja tema aset&auml;itja. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A working environment council shall elect the chairperson and his or her deputy from among its members. </inglise>
<eesti>N&otilde;ukogu v&otilde;tab otsused vastu konsensusp&otilde;him&otilde;ttel. </eesti>
<inglise>The council shall adopt resolutions by consensus. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&ouml;&ouml;andja teavitab t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogu moodustamisest T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohalikku asutust. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An employer shall notify the regional office of the Labour Inspectorate of the setting up of a working environment council. </inglise>
<eesti>N&otilde;ukogu liikmete nimed ja nende volituste kehtimise ajad pannakse v&auml;lja n&auml;htavale kohale. </eesti>
<inglise>The names and term of authority of the council members shall be displayed in a visible place. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogu: </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A working environment council shall: </inglise>
<eesti>1) anal&uuml;&uuml;sib korrap&auml;raselt ettev&otilde;tte t&ouml;&ouml;tingimusi, registreerib tekkivad probleemid ja teeb t&ouml;&ouml;andjale ettepanekuid nende lahendamiseks ning j&auml;lgib vastuv&otilde;etud otsuste t&auml;itmist; </eesti>
<inglise>1) regularly analyse the working conditions in the enterprise, document developing problems, make proposals to the employer for the resolution thereof and monitor the implementation of adopted resolutions; </inglise>
<eesti>2) osaleb ettev&otilde;tte t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse arenduskava ning ettev&otilde;tte rekonstrueerimise, remondi, tehnoloogiliste uuenduste ja muude plaanide koostamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) participate in the preparation of occupational health and safety strategies of the enterprise, plans for the reconstruction or repair of the enterprise and for the introduction of new technologies in the enterprise, and other plans; </inglise>
<eesti>3) tutvub ettev&otilde;tte t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna sisekontrolli tulemustega ning vajaduse korral teeb ettepanekuid puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) examine the results of internal controls of the working environment in the enterprise and, if necessary, make proposals for the elimination of deficiencies; </inglise>
<eesti>4) anal&uuml;&uuml;sib t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetusi ning kutsehaigestumisi ja muid t&ouml;&ouml;ga seotud haigestumisi ning j&auml;lgib, et t&ouml;&ouml;andja rakendab abin&otilde;usid nende ennetamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) analyse occupational accidents, cases of occupational disease and other illnesses related to work, and monitor the implementation of measures for the prevention thereof by the employer; </inglise>
<eesti>5) aitab luua naist&ouml;&ouml;tajatele ning alaealistele ja puudega t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele sobivad t&ouml;&ouml;tingimused ja t&ouml;&ouml;korralduse. </eesti>
<inglise>5) assist in the creation of suitable working conditions and work organisation for female workers, minors and disabled workers. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogu esitab oma ettepanekud t&ouml;&ouml;andjale kirjalikult. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) A working environment council shall communicate its proposals to the employer in writing. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja ei pea esitatud ettepanekute arvestamist v&otilde;imalikuks, esitab ta selle kohta n&otilde;ukogule ettepanekute saamisest arvates kolme n&auml;dala jooksul kirjaliku vastulause, milles p&otilde;hjendab arvestamata j&auml;tmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) If the employer does not consider it possible to take such proposals into account, the employer shall respond to the council in writing within three weeks after receipt of the proposals, providing reasons therefor. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui vastuolu j&auml;&auml;b p&uuml;sima, otsustab asja t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogu v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja avalduse alusel T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohaliku asutuse juhataja. </eesti>
<inglise>If the conflict is not resolved, the matter shall be decided by the head of the regional office of the Labour Inspectorate on the basis of an application of the working environment council or employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) T&ouml;&ouml;andja vabastab t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogu liikme p&otilde;hit&ouml;&ouml;st ajaks, mil ta t&auml;idab t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogu liikme kohustusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) An employer shall release a member of the working environment council from the duties of his or her principal job during the time when he or she performs the duties of a member of the working environment council. </inglise>
<eesti>N&otilde;ukogu liikmele s&auml;ilitatakse selleks ajaks keskmine t&ouml;&ouml;tasu ja tal on Eesti Vabariigi t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse &sect;-s 94 ning kollektiiv- ja t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus etten&auml;htud tagatised. </eesti>
<inglise>During this period, the member of the working environment council continues to receive his or her average wages and has the guarantees prescribed in &sect; 94 of the Republic of Estonia Employment Contracts Act, a collective agreement or the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>P&otilde;hit&ouml;&ouml;st vabastamise tingimused n&auml;hakse ette kollektiivlepingus v&otilde;i muus t&ouml;&ouml;andja ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate kirjalikus lepingus. </eesti>
<inglise>The conditions for release from the duties of a principal job shall be prescribed in a collective agreement or any other written contract between the employer and workers. </inglise>
<eesti>P&otilde;hit&ouml;&ouml;st vabastamise aeg ei tohi olla l&uuml;hem kui &uuml;ks tund n&auml;dalas. </eesti>
<inglise>The period of release from the duties of a principal job shall not be less than one hour per week. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogu liige on ka t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavolinik, siis kummakski t&ouml;&ouml;ks etten&auml;htud aeg liidetakse. </eesti>
<inglise>If a member of the working environment council also acts as a working environment representative, the time for performance of the duties of both jobs is totalled. </inglise>
<eesti>(10) T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogu liikmete v&auml;lja&otilde;ppe ja t&auml;iend&otilde;ppe korraldab t&ouml;&ouml;andja oma kulul ja t&ouml;&ouml;ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(10) An employer shall arrange for the training and in-service training of members of the working environment council at the employer's expense and during working hours. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;lja&otilde;ppe ja t&auml;iend&otilde;ppe ajaks s&auml;ilitatakse neile keskmine t&ouml;&ouml;tasu. </eesti>
<inglise>During training and in-service training, they continue to receive their average wages. </inglise>
<eesti>(11) T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogu informeerib igal aastal kirjalikult oma tegevusest T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohalikku asutust. </eesti>
<inglise>(11) A working environment council shall inform the regional office of the Labour Inspectorate annually of its activities in writing. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiuteenistus </eesti>
<inglise>Occupational health service </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiuteenistus on sotsiaalministri antud tegevusloa alusel t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiuteenuseid osutav asutus v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tte struktuuri&uuml;ksus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An occupational health service is an agency or a structural unit of an enterprise which provides occupational health services on the basis of an activity licence issued by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiuteenusena m&otilde;istetakse t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiuarsti v&otilde;i -&otilde;e, t&ouml;&ouml;h&uuml;gieeniku, t&ouml;&ouml;ps&uuml;hholoogi, ergonoomi v&otilde;i muu t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiuspetsialisti t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesande t&auml;itmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Occupational health services involve the performance of duties by occupational health doctors or nurses, occupational hygienists, occupational psychologists, ergonomists or other occupational health specialists. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiuteenistuse p&otilde;hi&uuml;lesanne on v&auml;ltida v&otilde;i v&auml;hendada ohtu t&ouml;&ouml;tajate tervisele ja ennetada kutset&ouml;&ouml;ga seotud haigestumisi. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The main purpose of an occupational health service is to prevent or reduce risks to the health of workers and to prevent contraction of occupational diseases. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiuteenistus osutab j&auml;rgmisi teenuseid: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An occupational health service shall provide the following services: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teeb t&ouml;&ouml;koha riskianal&uuml;&uuml;si, sealhulgas m&otilde;&otilde;dab t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna ohutegurite parameetreid, ning teeb ettepanekuid t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste parandamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) conducts risk assessments of workplaces, including measurements of the parameters of risk factors present in the working environment, and makes proposals for the improvement of the working conditions; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kontrollib ja j&auml;lgib t&ouml;&ouml;tajate tervise seisundit, et ennetada kutsehaiguste ja teiste t&ouml;&ouml;ga seotud haiguste kujunemist; </eesti>
<inglise>2) examines and monitors the state of health of workers to prevent the development of occupational diseases or other illnesses related to work; </inglise>
<eesti>3) aitab korraldada t&ouml;&ouml;tajate meditsiinilist ja kutsealast rehabilitatsiooni; </eesti>
<inglise>3) assists in the organisation of medical and occupational rehabilitation of workers; </inglise>
<eesti>4) annab t&ouml;&ouml;andjale n&otilde;u t&ouml;&ouml; kohandamisel t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;imetele ja tema tervise seisundile; </eesti>
<inglise>4) advises employers on the adaptation of work to the abilities and state of health of workers; </inglise>
<eesti>5) annab t&ouml;&ouml;andjale n&otilde;u t&ouml;&ouml;vahendite ja isikukaitsevahendite valimiseks ja kasutamiseks ning n&otilde;ustab muudes t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse k&uuml;simustes. </eesti>
<inglise>5) advises employers on the choice and use of work equipment and personal protective equipment and provides advice on other occupational health and safety issues. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiuteenistus j&auml;rgib oma t&ouml;&ouml;s kutse-eetika p&otilde;him&otilde;tteid: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) In its work, an occupational health service shall observe the principles of professional ethics by: </inglise>
<eesti>1) hoiab oma tegevuse t&otilde;ttu teatavaks saanud tootmis- ja &auml;risaladust, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui selle p&otilde;him&otilde;tte j&auml;rgimisest tuleb loobuda t&ouml;&ouml;tajate tervise ja ohutuse kaitseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) maintaining the confidentiality of production and business secrets which become known to it in the course of its activities, except if departure from this is required in order to protect the health and safety of workers; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kaitseb t&ouml;&ouml;tajate tervise- ja eraeluandmete konfidentsiaalsust; </eesti>
<inglise>2) protecting the confidentiality of information concerning the health and private life of workers; </inglise>
<eesti>3) teatab tervisekontrolli tulemustest ettev&otilde;tte juhtkonnale ainult seda, millised piirangud on t&ouml;&ouml;tajale t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks seatud tervise vastun&auml;idustuste t&otilde;ttu; </eesti>
<inglise>3) disclosing the results of health surveillance to the management of the enterprise only in terms of the restrictions imposed on the performance of duties by workers by reason of contraindications; </inglise>
<eesti>4) teavitab t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid kutset&ouml;&ouml;ga ja t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnaga seotud ohtudest objektiivselt. </eesti>
<inglise>4) providing objective information to workers concerning the risks associated with their professional acivities and the working environment. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) T&ouml;&ouml;tajate tervisekontrolli korra kehtestab sotsiaalminister oma m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The procedure for the health surveillance of workers shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiuteenuste osutamiseks antava tegevusloa taotlemise ja andmise korra kehtestab sotsiaalminister oma m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The procedure for application for and grant of activity licences for the provision of occupational health services shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu Keskus </eesti>
<inglise>Occupational Health Centre </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu Keskus on Sotsiaalministeeriumi hallatav riigiasutus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Occupational Health Centre is a state agency administered by the Ministry of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu Keskuse &uuml;lesanded on: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The functions of the Occupational Health Centre are to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teha t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu teadus- ja rakendusuuringuid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) conduct scientific and applied research into occupational health; </inglise>
<eesti>2) viia ellu t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiuprogrammid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) implement occupational health programmes; </inglise>
<eesti>3) anda eksperdihinnanguid t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiuga seotud k&uuml;simustes ning teha kutsehaiguse ekspertiisi; </eesti>
<inglise>3) provide expert assessments on occupational health issues and provide expert analyses of diagnoses of occupational diseases; </inglise>
<eesti>4) korraldada t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiuarstide ja -&otilde;dede ning teiste t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiuspetsialistide t&auml;iend&otilde;pet; </eesti>
<inglise>4) organise in-service training for occupational health doctors and nurses and other occupational health specialists; </inglise>
<eesti>5) koguda, anal&uuml;&uuml;sida ja edastada t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiuandmeid; </eesti>
<inglise>5) gather, analyse and disseminate occupational health information; </inglise>
<eesti>6) pidada arvestust kutsehaiguste kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>6) keep records of occupational diseases. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu Keskuse moodustab ja tema p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruse kinnitab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Occupational Health Centre shall be set up and its statutes shall be approved by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna N&otilde;ukoda </eesti>
<inglise>Advisory Committee on Working Environment </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna N&otilde;ukoda on Sotsiaalministeeriumi juures asuv valitsusasutuste ning t&ouml;&ouml;andjate ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate keskliitude t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse asjatundjatest koosnev n&otilde;uandekogu t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna k&uuml;simustes. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Advisory Committee on Working Environment is an advisory board within the Ministry of Social Affairs which deals with issues concerning the working environment and comprises occupational health and safety experts of government agencies, central associations of employers and central unions of employees. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) N&otilde;ukoja p&otilde;hi&uuml;lesanne on teha ettepanekuid ja avaldada arvamust t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnapoliitika v&auml;ljat&ouml;&ouml;tamiseks ja rakendamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The main function of the Advisory Committee is to make proposals for and express opinions on the development and implementation of the working environment policy. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) N&otilde;ukoda t&auml;idab j&auml;rgmisi &uuml;lesandeid: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Advisory Committee shall perform the following functions: </inglise>
<eesti>1) hindab korrap&auml;raselt riigi t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna seisundit; </eesti>
<inglise>1) regularly assesses the condition of working environments in the state; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kogub, vaatab l&auml;bi ja arutab sotsiaalpartnerite t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna parandamise ettepanekuid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) gathers, reviews and discusses proposals by social partners for improvement of the working environment; </inglise>
<eesti>3) anal&uuml;&uuml;sib t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna parandamise abin&otilde;ude t&otilde;husust; </eesti>
<inglise>3) analyses the effectiveness of measures for improvement of the working environment; </inglise>
<eesti>4) teeb sotsiaalministrile ettepanekuid ja annab soovitusi t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna k&uuml;simustes; </eesti>
<inglise>4) makes proposals and recommendations to the Minister of Social Affairs on working environment issues; </inglise>
<eesti>5) arutab Riigikogule, Vabariigi Valitsusele ja sotsiaalministrile esitatavate seaduste ja m&auml;&auml;ruste eeln&otilde;usid ning annab nendele hinnangu; </eesti>
<inglise>5) discusses draft Acts and regulations submitted to the Riigikogu (2), the Government of the Republic and the Minister of Social Affairs and provides assessments thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>6) teeb ettepanekuid &otilde;igusaktide muutmiseks ja t&auml;iendamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>6) makes proposals to amend legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna N&otilde;ukoja t&ouml;&ouml;kord kehtestatakse p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;rusega, mille kinnitab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The rules of procedure of the Advisory Committee on Working Environment shall be established by its statutes, which shall be approved by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>N&otilde;ukoja koosseisu kinnitab sotsiaalminister valitsusasutuste ning t&ouml;&ouml;andjate ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate keskliitude ettepanekute alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>The membership of the Advisory Committee shall be approved by the Minister of Social Affairs on the basis of proposals from government agencies, central associations of employers and central unions of employees. </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetus ja kutsehaigestumine </eesti>
<inglise>Occupational Accidents and Occupational Diseases </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetus </eesti>
<inglise>Occupational accident </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetus on &auml;kktervisekahjustus v&otilde;i surm, mis leiab aset t&ouml;&ouml;andja antud t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannet t&auml;ites v&otilde;i muul tema loal tehtaval t&ouml;&ouml;l, t&ouml;&ouml;aja hulka arvataval t&ouml;&ouml;vaheajal, t&ouml;&ouml;teel v&otilde;i muus t&ouml;&ouml;ga seotud olukorras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An occupational accident is sudden damage to health or death which occurs in the performance of a duty assigned by an employer or in other work performed with the employer's permission, during a break included in the working time, on the way to or from work, or in other cases related to work. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andja registreerib k&otilde;ik t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetused ja teeb sellekohased andmed teatavaks t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavolinikule, t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogu liikmetele, t&ouml;&ouml;tajate usaldusisikule ja t&ouml;&ouml;inspektorile. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employer shall register all occupational accidents and make relevant information available to the working environment representatives, members of the working environment council, workers' representatives and the labour inspector. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Raske t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetuse korral peab t&ouml;&ouml;andja sellest viivitamata teatama T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohalikule asutusele ning surmaga l&otilde;ppenud t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetuse korral ka politseile. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An employer shall report a serious occupational accident promptly to the regional office of the Labour Inspectorate and, if the occupational accident is fatal, the employer shall also inform the police. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja on t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetusest p&otilde;hjustatud tervisekahjustuse korral p&ouml;&ouml;rdunud t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuna arsti poole, teatab arst sellest kirjalikult T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohalikule asutusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a worker consults a doctor about damage to his or her health caused by an occupational accident as a result of which he or she has become incapacitated for work, the doctor shall notify the regional office of the Labour Inspectorate thereof in writing. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Kutsehaigus ja muu t&ouml;&ouml;ga seotud haigestumine </eesti>
<inglise>Occupational disease and other illnesses related to work </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kutsehaigus on t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna ohutegurist v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml; laadist p&otilde;hjustatud tervisekahjustus, mis on kantud kutsehaiguste loetelusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An occupational disease is damage to health which is brought about by risk factors present in the working environment or the nature of the work and which is included in the list of occupational diseases. </inglise>
<eesti>Kutsehaiguste loetelu kehtestab sotsiaalminister oma m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The list of occupational diseases shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;tajal kutsehaigust v&otilde;i muud t&ouml;&ouml;ga seotud haigust kahtlustav arst saadab t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiuarsti juurde. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A doctor who suspects that a worker is suffering from an occupational disease or any other illness related to work shall refer the worker to an occupational health doctor. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kutsehaiguse diagnoosib t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiuarst, kes kogub selleks andmed t&ouml;&ouml;taja praeguste ja varasemate t&ouml;&ouml;olude ja t&ouml;&ouml; laadi kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An occupational disease shall be diagnosed by an occupational health doctor, who, for such purpose, shall gather information concerning the worker's current and previous working conditions and the nature of his or her work. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;andja registreerib k&otilde;ik kutsehaigusjuhud ja muud t&ouml;&ouml;st p&otilde;hjustatud haigestumised ning teeb sellekohased andmed k&auml;ttesaadavaks t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnaspetsialistile, t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavolinikule, t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogu liikmetele ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate usaldusisikule ning teavitab nendest T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohalikku asutust. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An employer shall register all cases of occupational disease and other illnesses related to work, and shall make relevant information available to the working environment specialists, working environment representatives, members of the working environment council and workers' representatives, and shall notify the regional office of the Labour Inspectorate thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiuarst teatab kutsehaigusest t&ouml;&ouml;andjale, T&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu Keskusele ja T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohalikule asutusele, t&ouml;&ouml;st p&otilde;hjustatud muust haigusest t&ouml;&ouml;andjale ja T&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu Keskusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An occupational health doctor shall notify the employer, the Occupational Health Centre and the regional office of the Labour Inspectorate of cases of occupational disease, and shall notify the employer and the Occupational Health Centre of other illnesses related to work. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetuse ja kutsehaigestumise uurimine </eesti>
<inglise>Investigation of occupational accidents and cases of occupational disease </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetuse ja kutsehaigestumise asjaolud ja p&otilde;hjused selgitab uurimine, mille viib l&auml;bi t&ouml;&ouml;andja ning milles h&auml;&auml;le&otilde;igusega peab osalema t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavolinik, selle puudumisel t&ouml;&ouml;tajate usaldusisik. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The circumstances of an occupational accident or of the contraction of an occupational disease and reasons therefor shall be established in the course of an investigation which is carried out by the employer and in which a working environment representative or, in his or her absence, a workers' representative shall participate with the right to vote. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui t&ouml;&ouml;andjal puuduvad vajalikud teadmised, peab ta uurimisse kaasama p&auml;deva eksperdi. </eesti>
<inglise>If the employer lacks necessary knowledge, the employer shall involve a competent expert in the investigation. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andja esitab uurimistulemuste kohta kirjaliku raporti kannatanule v&otilde;i tema huvide kaitsjale, T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohalikule asutusele ja kindlustusasutusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The employer shall submit a written report on the investigation results to the victim or a person representing his or her interests, the regional office of the Labour Inspectorate and to the insurance company. </inglise>
<eesti>Raportis nimetatakse abin&otilde;ud, mida t&ouml;&ouml;andja rakendab samalaadse t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetuse ja kutsehaiguse ennetamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>The report shall indicate measures to be implemented by the employer to prevent a similar occupational accident or the contraction of a similar occupational disease. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;andja teeb uurimistulemused teatavaks t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele v&otilde;i nende esindajale ja t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogule. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The employer shall notify the workers or their representatives and the working environment council of the investigation results. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;inspektor uurib raskeid v&otilde;i surmaga l&otilde;ppenud t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetusi ja kutsehaigusjuhtumeid t&ouml;&ouml;andjast s&otilde;ltumatult. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Labour inspectors shall investigate serious or fatal occupational accidents and cases of occupational disease independently of employers. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetuse ja kutsehaigestumise uurimise andmeid s&auml;ilitatakse 55 aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Information concerning investigations of occupational accidents or cases of occupational disease shall be preserved for fifty-five years. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) T&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetuse ja kutsehaigestumise uurimise ja registreerimise korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The procedure for investigation and registration of occupational accidents and cases of occupational disease shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>6. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 6 </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklik j&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>State supervision </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsioon </eesti>
<inglise>Labour Inspectorate </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsioon on Sotsiaalministeeriumi valitsemisalas tegutsev valitsusasutus, kelle p&otilde;hi&uuml;lesanne on: </eesti>
<inglise>The Labour Inspectorate is a government agency operating within the area of government of the Ministry of Social Affairs, whose main functions are to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) korraldada riiklikku j&auml;relevalvet t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnas t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoidu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutust ning t&ouml;&ouml;suhteid reguleerivate &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmise &uuml;le; </eesti>
<inglise>1) arrange for the exercise of state supervision in the working environment over compliance with the requirements of legislation regulating occupational health and safety and labour relations; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kohaldada riiklikku sundi seadusega etten&auml;htud alustel ja ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>2) apply enforcement by the state on the bases and to the extent prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;inspektor </eesti>
<inglise>Labour inspector </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;inspektor on T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni ametnik, kes teostab riiklikku j&auml;relevalvet t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoidu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutust ning t&ouml;&ouml;suhteid reguleerivate &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmise &uuml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A labour inspector is an official of the Labour Inspectorate who exercises state supervision over compliance with the requirements of legislation regulating occupational health and safety, and labour relations. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;inspektor on oma &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel s&otilde;ltumatu ja otsuste tegemisel erapooletu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Labour inspectors shall be independent in performing their duties and impartial in making decisions. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;inspektor on kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A labour inspector is required: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kontrollima t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoidu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutust ning t&ouml;&ouml;suhteid reguleerivate &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmist ettev&otilde;ttes; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to monitor compliance by an enterprise with the requirements of legislation regulating occupational health and safety and labour relations; </inglise>
<eesti>2) uurima raskeid v&otilde;i surmaga l&otilde;ppenud t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetusi ja kutsehaigusjuhtumeid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to investigate serious or fatal occupational accidents and cases of occupational disease; </inglise>
<eesti>3) teostama j&auml;relevalvet t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetuste uurimise &uuml;le ning abin&otilde;ude rakendamise &uuml;le t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetuste ja kutsehaiguste ennetamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) to exercise supervision over investigations of occupational accidents and over the implementation of measures for the prevention of occupational accidents and occupational diseases; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kontrollima enne kohaliku omavalitsuse poolt uuele v&otilde;i rekonstrueeritud ehitisele kasutusloa andmist selle vastavust t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>4) before the local government grants an authorisation to use a new or reconstructed building, to check the conformity of the building to the occupational health and safety requirements; </inglise>
<eesti>5) hoidma talle teenistuse t&otilde;ttu teatavaks saanud tootmis- v&otilde;i &auml;risaladust, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui avalikustamisn&otilde;ue tuleneb seadusest; </eesti>
<inglise>5) to maintain the confidentiality of production or business secrets which become known to him or her in the course of performing his or her duties, except if the duty to disclose such information is provided by law; </inglise>
<eesti>6) j&auml;tma t&ouml;&ouml;andjale ja teistele isikutele avaldamata selle isiku andmed, kes on teatanud t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnas ilmnevatest puudustest ning t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoidu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutust ning t&ouml;&ouml;suhteid reguleerivate &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmisest, kui isik ei soovi oma andmeid avaldada; </eesti>
<inglise>6) not to disclose information to the employer or others concerning a person who has notified him or her of deficiencies present in the working environment or of non-compliance with the requirements of legislation regulating occupational health and safety and labour relations, unless the person wishes such information to be disclosed; </inglise>
<eesti>7) peatama t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i teiste isikute elule ohtliku t&ouml;&ouml; tegemise ning keelama eluohtliku t&ouml;&ouml;vahendi kasutamise. </eesti>
<inglise>7) to stop work which is dangerous to the life of workers or that of other persons, and to prohibit the use of life-threatening work equipment. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;inspektoril on &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A labour inspector has the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) peatada t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i teiste isikute elule ohtliku t&ouml;&ouml; tegemine ning keelata eluohtliku t&ouml;&ouml;vahendi kasutamine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) stop work which is dangerous to the life of workers or that of other persons, and prohibit the use of life-threatening work equipment; </inglise>
<eesti>2) teha t&ouml;&ouml;andjale ettekirjutusi t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoidu, t&ouml;&ouml;ohutust ja t&ouml;&ouml;suhteid reguleerivate &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise korral ja kontrollida ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmist; </eesti>
<inglise>2) issue precepts to an employer in the case of non-compliance with the requirements of legislation regulating occupational health and safety, and labour relations, and monitor compliance with such precepts; </inglise>
<eesti>3) seaduses etten&auml;htud alustel ja ulatuses kohaldada halduskaristust, kui ei ole t&auml;idetud t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoidu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutust ning t&ouml;&ouml;suhteid reguleerivate &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;udeid, v&otilde;i koostada ja esitada p&auml;devale ametiisikule haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise protokoll; </eesti>
<inglise>3) impose administrative penalties on the grounds and to the extent prescribed by law if the requirements of legislation regulating occupational health and safety, and labour relations are not complied with, or to prepare and submit reports on administrative offences to competent officials; </inglise>
<eesti>4) rakendada meetmeid, mida ta peab vajalikuks selleks, et veenduda &otilde;igusaktide ranges t&auml;itmises, sealhulgas p&auml;&auml;seda t&ouml;&ouml;andja valduses olevasse ettev&otilde;ttesse, k&uuml;sitleda kas &uuml;ksinda v&otilde;i tunnistajate juuresolekul t&ouml;&ouml;andjat, usaldusisikut ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu, t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse ja t&ouml;&ouml;suhete kohta, tutvuda dokumentidega, mida t&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud pidama, ja teha neist koopiaid ja v&auml;ljav&otilde;tteid, n&otilde;uda t&ouml;&ouml;andjalt t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna kontrollm&otilde;&otilde;tmiste tegemist, pildistada ning v&otilde;tta materjalidest v&otilde;i ainetest proove anal&uuml;&uuml;siks. </eesti>
<inglise>4) take any measure which he or she may consider necessary in order to satisfy himself or herself that the legislation is strictly observed and, in particular, to access an enterprise in the possession of an employer; question, alone or in the presence of witnesses, the employer, workers' representative and workers about occupational health and safety and labour relations; examine documents that the employer is required to keep and copy or make extracts of such documents; demand that the employer conduct audit measurements of the working environment; take photographs; and take samples from materials or substances for analysis. </inglise>
<eesti>7. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 7 </inglise>
<eesti>Vaidluste lahendamine ja vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Dispute Resolution and Liability </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>Vaidluste lahendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Resolution of disputes </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse kohaldamisel t&ouml;&ouml;andja ja t&ouml;&ouml;taja vahel tekkinud vaidlused lahendatakse seaduses etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Disputes arising between employers and workers in the application of this Act shall be resolved pursuant to the procedure prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui juriidiline v&otilde;i f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik ei n&otilde;ustu t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse riiklikku j&auml;relevalvet teostava t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori ettekirjutuse v&otilde;i muu toiminguga, on tal &otilde;igus esitada T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohaliku asutuse juhatajale kaebus ettekirjutuse saamisest v&otilde;i muu toimingu tegemisest arvates k&uuml;mne kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a legal or natural person does not agree with a precept or any other act of a labour inspector exercising state supervision in occupational health and safety matters, the person has the right to file a complaint with the head of the regional office of the Labour Inspectorate within ten calendar days after receipt of the precept or performance of the act. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaebuse esitamine ei vabasta kohustusest ettekirjutust t&auml;ita. </eesti>
<inglise>The filing of a complaint shall not discharge the person from the obligation to comply with the precept. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohaliku asutuse juhataja vaatab kaebuse l&auml;bi ning teeb oma otsuse - kas j&auml;tta ettekirjutus v&otilde;i m&otilde;ni muu toiming j&otilde;usse, see muuta v&otilde;i t&uuml;histada - kaebuse saamise p&auml;evast arvates kahe n&auml;dala jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The head of the regional office of the Labour Inspectorate shall review the complaint and make a decision on whether the precept or act remains in force, or whether to amend or invalidate it, within two weeks after the date of receipt of the complaint. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsus tehakse kaebuse esitajale teatavaks ning antakse k&auml;tte allkirja vastu v&otilde;i saadetakse posti teel v&auml;ljastusteatega. </eesti>
<inglise>The person who filed the appeal or objection shall be notified of the decision, which shall be delivered to the person against a signature or sent by post with advice of delivery. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui kaebaja T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohaliku asutuse juhataja otsusega ei n&otilde;ustu, v&otilde;ib ta selle vaidlustada halduskohtus. </eesti>
<inglise>If the complainant does not agree with the decision of the head of the regional office of the Labour Inspectorate, the complainant may appeal it in an administrative court. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kaebuse esitamine halduskohtule ei v&otilde;ta isikult kohustust t&auml;ita t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori ettekirjutust seni, kuni kohus tunnistab selle kas osaliselt v&otilde;i t&auml;ielikult seadusevastaseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The filing of an appeal with an administrative court shall not discharge the person from the obligation to comply with the precept of the labour inspector until the court has declared it illegal in part or in whole. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Liability </inglise>
<eesti>(1) F&uuml;&uuml;siline isik kannab k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uete rikkumise eest distsiplinaar-, haldus-, kriminaal- v&otilde;i tsiviilvastutust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A natural person shall bear disciplinary, administrative, criminal or civil liability for violation of the requirements of this Act or legislation issued on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Juriidiline isik kannab k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uete rikkumise eest haldusvastutust j&auml;rgmises ulatuses: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A legal person shall bear administrative liability for violation of the requirements of this Act or legislation issued on the basis thereof as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) &otilde;igusakti n&otilde;ude t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise eest, kui see p&otilde;hjustab surmaga l&otilde;ppeva &otilde;nnetuse, samuti t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori ettekirjutuses m&auml;rgitud &otilde;igusakti n&otilde;ude korduva t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv kuni 250 000 krooni; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a fine of up to 250 000 kroons shall be imposed for non-compliance with requirements of legislation if this causes a fatal accident, and for repeated non-compliance with requirements of legislation indicated in a precept of a labour inspector; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &otilde;igusakti n&otilde;ude t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise eest, kui see p&otilde;hjustab raske tagaj&auml;rjega t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetuse v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse kutsehaiguse tagaj&auml;rjel - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv kuni 100 000 krooni; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a fine of up to 100 000 kroons shall be imposed for non-compliance with requirements of legislation if this causes a serious occupational accident or incapacity for work as a result of an occupational disease; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetuse v&otilde;i kutsehaigestumise varjamise, nende uurimata j&auml;tmise v&otilde;i raporti koostamata j&auml;tmise, t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavoliniku uurimisse mittekaasamise, t&ouml;&ouml;tajale tervisekontrolli tegemata j&auml;tmise ning naist&ouml;&ouml;tajate, alaealiste v&otilde;i puudega t&ouml;&ouml;tajate t&ouml;&ouml;piirangute j&auml;rgimata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv kuni 50 000 krooni; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a fine of up to 50 000 kroons shall be imposed for concealment of an occupational accident or in case of occupational disease, for failure to investigate same or prepare a report, to involve a working environment representative in the investigation, to conduct the health surveillance of a worker, or for non-compliance with the restrictions on the work of female workers, minors or disabled workers; </inglise>
<eesti>4) uue v&otilde;i rekonstrueeritud ehitise kasutuselev&otilde;tmise eest ilma t&ouml;&ouml;inspektori n&otilde;usolekuta - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv kuni 50 000 krooni; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a fine of up to 50 000 kroons shall be imposed for commencement of use of a new or reconstructed building without the authorisation of a labour inspector; </inglise>
<eesti>5) t&ouml;&ouml;tajale v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tajate esindajale etten&auml;htud t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse koolituse korraldamata j&auml;tmise, t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna ohutegurite parameetrite m&otilde;&otilde;tmata j&auml;tmise ning t&ouml;&ouml;tajale ohutegurile vastava isikukaitsevahendi andmata j&auml;tmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv kuni 20 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>5) a fine of up to 20 000 kroons shall be imposed for failure to arrange for prescribed training in occupational health and safety for workers or workers' representatives, for failure to measure the parameters of risk factors present in the working environment and for failure to provide the workers with personal protective equipment corresponding to the risk factors. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik, tegutsedes juriidilise isiku nimel v&otilde;i huvides, rikkus k&auml;esoleva seaduse v&otilde;i selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;udeid, on &otilde;iguserikkumise eest vastutavad m&otilde;lemad ning haldusvastutust v&otilde;ib kohaldada nii juriidilisele kui ka f&uuml;&uuml;silisele isikule. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a natural person acting in the name or interest of a legal person violates requirements of this Act or legislation issued on the basis thereof, both the natural person and legal person are liable for the offence and may be held administratively liable. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>Menetlus juriidilise isiku &otilde;iguserikkumise asjas </eesti>
<inglise>Proceedings concerning offences by legal persons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 28 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud &otilde;iguserikkumise asja arutamise ja halduskaristuse m&auml;&auml;ramise &otilde;igus on halduskohtunikul ja T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohaliku asutuse juhatajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Administrative court judges and heads of the regional offices of the Labour Inspectorate have the right to hear matters concerning the offences and to impose the administrative penalties specified in subsection 28 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohaliku asutuse juhatajal on k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 28 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud &otilde;iguserikkumise asjas &otilde;igus m&auml;&auml;rata rahatrahv kuni 30 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The head of a regional office of the Labour Inspectorate has the right to impose a fine of up to 30 000 kroons in matters concerning the offences specified in subsection 28 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Menetlus k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 28 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise asjas, kaasa arvatud karistuse m&auml;&auml;ramine, selle vaidlustamine ja j&otilde;ustunud halduskaristuse otsuse t&auml;itmine toimub haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustikus (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 1999, 41, 496; 45, &otilde;iend) ja t&auml;itemenetluse seadustikus (RT I 1993, 49, 693; 1997, 43/44, 723; 1998, 41/42, 625; 51, 756; 61, 981; 103, 1695; 1999, 18, 302; 27, 380; 95, 845; 2000, 28, 167; 35, 222) s&auml;testatud korras, kui k&auml;esolev seadus ei n&auml;e ette teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Proceedings concerning the administrative offences specified in subsection 28 (2) of this Act, including the imposition of penalties, contesting thereof and enforcement of a judgement which has entered into force concerning an administrative penalty, are conducted pursuant to the procedure provided by the Code of Administrative Offences (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 1999, 41, 496; 45, Correction Notice) and the Code of Enforcement Procedure (RT I 1993, 49, 693; 1997, 43/44, 723; 1998, 41/42, 625; 51, 756; 61, 981; 103, 1695; 1999, 18, 302; 27, 380; 95, 845; 2000, 28, 167; 35, 222), unless otherwise provided by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
<eesti>Haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise protokolli koostamine </eesti>
<inglise>Preparation of minutes of administrative offences </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 28 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste kohta on &otilde;igus protokolli koostada T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohaliku asutuse juhataja volitatud ametnikul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official authorised by the head of a regional office of the Labour Inspectorate has the right to prepare reports on the administrative offences provided for in subsection 28 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise protokolli m&auml;rgitakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A report on an administrative offence shall set out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) selle koostamise aeg ja koht; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the time and place of its preparation; </inglise>
<eesti>2) asutuse nimetus ja aadress, kelle nimel protokoll koostatakse; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the name and address of the agency in whose name the report is prepared; </inglise>
<eesti>3) protokolli koostanud isiku ametinimetus, ees- ja perekonnanimi; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the official title and the given name and surname of the person who prepared the report; </inglise>
<eesti>4) haldus&otilde;iguserikkujaks olnud juriidilise isiku nimetus v&otilde;i &auml;rinimi, registreerimise number ja asukoht ning tema esindaja ametikoht, ees- ja perekonnanimi; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the name or business name, registration number and location of the legal person who is the administrative offender, and the position and the given name and surname of the legal person's representative; </inglise>
<eesti>5) haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise koht, aeg ja kirjeldus; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the place, time and description of the administrative offence; </inglise>
<eesti>6) haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja esindaja seletus; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the explanation of the representative of the administrative offender; </inglise>
<eesti>7) muud asja lahendamiseks vajalikud andmed. </eesti>
<inglise>7) other information necessary for the resolution of the matter. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Protokollile kirjutavad alla selle koostanud isik ja haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja esindaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A report shall be signed by the person who prepares the report and the representative of the administrative offender. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja esindaja keeldub protokollile alla kirjutamast, tehakse sellesse vastav kanne. </eesti>
<inglise>If the representative of the administrative offender refuses to sign the report, a corresponding entry shall be made therein. </inglise>
<eesti>Protokollile lisatakse haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja esindaja kirjalikud m&auml;rkused protokolli, samuti protokollile allakirjutamisest keeldumise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>The written comments of the representative of the administrative offender concerning the report or refusal to sign the report shall be annexed to the report. </inglise>
<eesti>8. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
